<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="24.[189,303,1369,1395]" box="[189,303,1369,1395]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,1369,1395]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,1369,1395]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[189,1399,1415,1548]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
This taxon was initially introduced as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Trovao" authorityYear="1979" box="[822,965,1416,1442]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="verdensis">
<emphasis box="[822,965,1416,1442]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">A. verdensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This species has not been examined molecularly. However, the geographic isolation of 
<collectingRegion box="[806,876,1451,1477]" country="Cape Verde" name="Brava" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Brava</collectingRegion>
Island within the 
<collectingCountry box="[1103,1244,1451,1477]" name="Cape Verde" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Cabo Verde</collectingCountry>
Archipelago together with the distinctive morphology of shell and radula suggest that this is most likely a valid species, well differentiated in genetic distance from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Trovao" authorityYear="1979" box="[801,943,1521,1548]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="verdensis">
<emphasis box="[801,943,1521,1548]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">A. verdensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
